The evidence with the title 'New York City Crime Falls But just why is a mystery - nytimes.com ' says Jan 1, 1995  ... Whatever the reason , the fact is that in a variety of neighborhoods across the city -- rich , poor and in between -- reports of serious crime fell significantly in 1994,  ... In East New York , Brooklyn , which in 1993 had the most homicides of any neighborhood , with 126, murders fell by more than a quarter. 
